$$\mathrm{IQR} ={ \mathrm{x}}_{.25} -{\mathrm{x}}_{.75}$$
\end{document} where x. 25 and x. 75 refer to the value of the variable (e.g., age at death) at the first and third quartile, and 6.2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
