$$\mathrm{RIQR} = (\mathrm{IQR} \div {\mathrm{x}}_{\mathrm{md}}) {_\ast} 100$$
\end{document} where the IQR is divided by the median, or second quartile, so as to adjust for the level of the distribution and “isolate” the degree of dispersion. For the standard deviation and the coefficient of variation, 6.3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
