				\begin{document}
$$\begin{array}{rcl} \mathrm{CV} = (\sigma \div {\mathrm{x}}_{\mathrm{m}}) {_\ast} 100& &\end{array}$$
\end{document} where, to derive the coefficient of variation, the standard deviation is divided by the mean. (To simplify the computations, the mean deviation \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
